<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Self-serve dispenser service</p>
    <h2>A different category from production ice machines.</h2>

    <p>Self-serve ice dispensers are a distinct category from production ice machines. Hotel hallway dispensers serve thousands of guests per week. Healthcare cafeteria dispensers operate 24/7 for staff and visitors. Hospitality dispensers in hotel restaurants handle peak service rushes. When a dispenser fails, hundreds of users immediately notice, which makes dispenser uptime a hospitality priority that production ice machines don't quite match.</p>

    <p>Our techs service dispensers across LA, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, Riverside. Top brands: <strong>Cornelius</strong> (Marmon Foodservice Technologies, owned by Berkshire Hathaway, dominates the QSR and hospitality dispenser market with combo ice + water + carbonated beverage units in the Pro-Series and Cyclone lines). <strong>Hoshizaki dispensers</strong> (DBF-25CH counter-top, DM-200B-LP under-counter, paired with KM-Edge ice production for hospitality installations). <strong>Manitowoc dispensers</strong> (DBF series, paired with Indigo NXT or as standalone). <strong>Follett</strong> (medical-grade dispensers for hospitals, designed for sanitary healthcare environments). <strong>Lancer</strong> (smaller specialty dispenser brand).</p>

    <p><strong>Architecture varies by configuration:</strong> ice-only dispensers (vend ice from a connected production ice machine), ice + water dispensers (add filtered water dispensing), ice + water + carbonated beverage (add CO2-charged beverage system, where Cornelius is the market leader), and self-contained dispensers (ice production AND dispensing integrated into a single unit, like Hoshizaki DCM Cubelet and Follett medical units).</p>

    <p>EPA 608 Universal certified (#1346255700410) for sealed-system work on self-contained units. R-290 hydrocarbon certification for newer green refrigerant dispensers. BHGS #A49573. BBB A+. Phones answered 24/7.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 TYPICAL FAILURES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Failure tree</p>
    <h2>Typical dispenser failures, by frequency.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Ten failure modes cover roughly 95% of dispenser service calls. The vend mechanism is dispenser-specific (no production ice machine has it), which is why general ice-machine techs sometimes misdiagnose dispenser issues.</p>

    <ol class="num-list">
      <li><strong>Vend actuator mechanism wear (year 5 to 8), most common dispenser-specific failure.</strong> The actuator that releases ice when the button is pressed wears with high cycle count (200+ vends per day on hotel hallways). Replacement $290 to $440.</li>
      <li><strong>Vend solenoid valve failure.</strong> Water-side dispenser solenoid that controls water flow. Year 4 to 7 typical.</li>
      <li><strong>Ice agitator motor failure.</strong> Motor inside ice storage bin that keeps ice from clumping. When it fails, ice clumps and the dispenser jams. $260 to $420.</li>
      <li><strong>Water inlet valve replacement.</strong> Same failure mode as production ice machines.</li>
      <li><strong>Cleaning service (preventive maintenance critical).</strong> Dispensers handle high user touch contact. Biological growth in chute and ice storage requires more frequent sanitization than production machines. Standard $200 to $340 plus sanitization specific to dispenser chute.</li>
      <li><strong>Vend chute cleaning plus sanitization.</strong> Biological buildup in the chute path is a health code issue, not just a cleanliness issue.</li>
      <li><strong>Water filter replacement (combo units with water dispensing).</strong> Typical 6-month replacement cycle, more often in hard water areas like the Inland Empire.</li>
      <li><strong>Refrigerant leak (self-contained dispensers with integrated ice production).</strong> EPA 608 leak repair before recharge. R-290 systems require R-290 certification.</li>
      <li><strong>Carbonated beverage system service (Cornelius combo units).</strong> CO2 lines and beverage syrup lines. Note: we service the refrigeration side. Beverage syrup service is specialty bar and soda trade.</li>
      <li><strong>Control board / vend logic replacement (year 8 to 12 modern dispensers).</strong> Modern dispensers with touch control panels. Cornelius Pro-Series and newer Hoshizaki dispensers fall into this category at end of life.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 INDUSTRY-SPECIFIC NOTES -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Industry context</p>
    <h2>Different installation environments, different service priorities.</h2>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Hotel hallway dispensers</h3>
    <p>Heavy public access, 200 to 500+ vends per day on active hotel floors. Sanitation critical (public-touch surfaces). Common installations: Cornelius Pro-200E, Hoshizaki DM-200B-LP, Follett. We service hotel chains (Marriott, Hilton, Hyatt) coordinated through facility managers. Multi-floor and multi-property fleet scheduling is standard for these accounts.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Healthcare cafeteria dispensers</h3>
    <p>Hospital staff and visitors, 24/7 operation. Patient floor dispensers serve specifically (medical-grade requirements with stricter sanitation protocols and material specifications). Common: Follett medical-grade dispensers, Hoshizaki DBF series. Hospital procurement coordinates through facility managers, often with specific compliance documentation requirements for the repair work.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Hospitality restaurant dispensers</h3>
    <p>Front-of-house dispensers in hotel restaurants, cafés, country club dining. Aesthetic matters (polished stainless, custom branding panels). Common: Cornelius Pro-Series customized, Hoshizaki dispensers with custom panels. We respect the front-of-house finish during service work, no scratched panels.</p>

    <h3 class="series-h3">Quick-service restaurant dispensers (QSR)</h3>
    <p>Combo ice + water + carbonated beverage units. Cornelius dominates this segment because the combo architecture is hard to replicate. Beverage syrup service (CO2 lines, BIB connections, syrup pump maintenance) is specialty bar and soda trade. We service the refrigeration and ice side only. We coordinate with bar and soda specialists when a combo unit needs both kinds of work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 REAL REPAIR STORIES -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">Real repairs</p>
    <h2>Composite stories from the route.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Five dispenser jobs from the past 90 days. Models, symptoms, diagnosis, parts, time, total. Names omitted; the technical scenarios are typical of what we see weekly.</p>

    <div class="story-grid">
      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hotel, Marina del Rey. Cornelius Pro-200E countertop ice + water dispenser, 5 years old.</h3>
        <p>Ice button not dispensing despite ice in the bin. Diagnosed: vend actuator mechanism worn (heavy hospitality use, 250+ vends per day estimated). Replaced actuator with Cornelius OEM. Cleaned dispenser chute and sanitized. Total: $120 plus $290 part plus 1 hour = $470. Hotel ops manager appreciated the speed of the visit.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Hospital cafeteria, Pasadena. Follett 7CI100A-S medical-grade nugget dispenser, 8 years old.</h3>
        <p>Ice clumping in storage bin. Diagnosed: ice agitator motor failed. Replaced motor with Follett OEM (medical-grade specification matters here, not a generic agitator motor). Sanitized ice storage bin to medical-grade protocol. Total: $120 plus $340 part plus 1.5 hours = $560. Documentation provided for hospital compliance records.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Marriott hotel hallway dispensers (5 units), Beverly Hills. Hoshizaki DM-200B-LP, 6 to 7 years old.</h3>
        <p>Facility manager called for fleet service. Diagnosed: 3 of 5 had vend actuator wear, 1 had water inlet valve issue, 1 had ice agitator motor needing replacement. Coordinated single visit, replaced 3 actuators plus 1 inlet valve plus 1 agitator motor. Total: $120 plus $1,180 parts plus 4.5 hours = $1,720 across the fleet. Hotel facilities manager appreciated single-call fleet coordination instead of 5 separate dispatches.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Healthcare facility, Santa Monica. Hoshizaki DBF-25CH counter-top dispenser, 7 years old, R-134a self-contained.</h3>
        <p>Refrigerant leak. Machine had been needing top-off (previous shop violating EPA 608 by recharging without leak repair). EPA 608 leak detection found a brazed evaporator joint leak. Repaired the joint, evacuated to 500 microns, recharged R-134a to spec. Now compliant with leak-repair-before-recharge regulation. Total: $120 plus $380 refrigerant plus $620 labor plus leak detection = $1,220.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="story-card">
        <h3>Country club restaurant, Calabasas. Cornelius Pro-Series customized panel dispenser, 9 years old.</h3>
        <p>Touch control panel non-responsive intermittently. Diagnosed: control board end-of-life (typical 9 to 12 year service life on modern dispenser control boards). Replaced board (Cornelius / Marmon parts via Berkshire Hathaway distribution, 5-day standard ship). Total: $120 plus $580 board plus $290 labor across 2 visits = $990. Custom branding panel preserved during repair.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 HONEST SCOPE -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">Scope</p>
    <h2>What we do, and what we don't.</h2>

    <p><strong>We service:</strong></p>
    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li>Cornelius dispensers (Pro-200E, Pro-Series customized, Cyclone, ice-only and ice + water variants)</li>
      <li>Hoshizaki dispensers (DBF-25CH counter-top, DM-200B-LP under-counter, plus integrated DCM Cubelet)</li>
      <li>Manitowoc dispensers (DBF series, paired with Indigo NXT or standalone)</li>
      <li>Follett medical-grade dispensers (hospital and clinic applications)</li>
      <li>Lancer specialty dispensers</li>
      <li>All dispenser configurations (ice-only, ice + water, self-contained ice production + dispensing)</li>
      <li>All EPA-permitted refrigerants for self-contained dispensers (R-22 legacy, R-134a, R-404A, R-290 hydrocarbon, with separate R-290 certification held)</li>
      <li>Vend mechanism service (actuators, solenoids, agitators)</li>
      <li>Chute cleaning plus sanitization to health code standards</li>
      <li>Multi-unit hotel chain fleet service coordination (Marriott, Hilton, Hyatt corporate accounts)</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong>We don't do:</strong> new dispenser installation (specialty installer trade); carbonated beverage syrup service on Cornelius combo units (specialty bar and soda trade, separate licensing, we service ice + water + refrigeration sides only); CO2 line installation or service (specialty gas distribution trade); custom branding panel installation on hospitality dispensers (sheet metal and sign trade, though we work around existing custom panels during repair).</p>

    <p>If you're not sure whether your dispenser falls under our scope, call. We tell you on the phone, before the dispatch fee, whether the work is ours or whether you need a different trade.</p>
  </div>
</section>

